				<text>10.2.2.7  Reals and Im to polar</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<ol class="HELM_parts">
<p>Convert the following numbers to polar form by replacing <i>r</i> and <i>theta</i> by appropriate precise values:</p>

<li><p> \( z_1 = {@z1@} = \) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]</p></li>

<li><p> \( z_2 = {@z2@} = \) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt2]]</p></li></ol>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<ol class="HELM_parts">
  <li>
<p> \( z_1 = {@z1@} \) is a real number so \( r = |z| = {@rval_r@} \) and \( \theta = {@principaltheta_r@} \). So, we can write \(z_1\) in polar form as: \( z_1 = {@ta1@}\).</p>
  </li>
  <li>
<p>&nbsp;\( z_2 = {@z2@} \) is an imaginary number so \( r = |z| = {@rval_i@} \) and \( \theta = {@principaltheta_i@} \). So, we can write \(z_2\) in polar form as: \( z_2 = {@ta2@}\).</p>
  </li>
</ol>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
